
# awsCostMonitor

This is an AWS cost monitoring utility to fetch daily costs through cloudcheckr apis and present statistics on a kibana dashboard

## VM Setup Steps

. Install Vagrant
. Install Virtual box
. Modify Vagrant.config to sync your awsCostMonitor folder
. Open a terminal window, then run the command
   Vagrant up
. run "Vagrant ssh" to connect to the VM
. to run the application, go the the awsCostMonitor folder, then run command: "grails run"

## OSX Commands:
 - Start Mongodb:
   mongod

 - Start elasticsearch:
   cd elasticsearch-5.4.1/bin
   ./elasticsearch

 - Start kibana:
   cd kibana-5.4.1-darwin-x86_64/bin
   ./kibana


CloudCheckr Restful API
https://api.cloudcheckr.com/api/billing.json/get_monthly_bill?access_key=[key]&aws_account_id=[id]&for_date=11-24-2017